  "text": "In this paper I use this phenomenon to derive fluctuation theorems and thermodynamic uncertainty relations for systems that comprise multiple interacting subsystems. Following the pioneering work of [CITATION_1] , I formulate the interactions of those subsystems as (extensions of) Bayesian networks. However, in contrast to the work in [CITATION_2] , I choose the subsystems to ensure that the expected EP of each one is non-negative. (This in fact is crucial for deriving the uncertainty relations.) In addition, whereas [CITATION_3] only derived a fluctuation theorem concerning a single one of the subsystems, I derive a set of fluctuation theorems that concern the dynamics of the full system.",
